entries.title: Self-care routines
entries.entry: I've been trying to take better care of myself lately. I've been trying to get more sleep, eat healthier, and exercise more. It's been a bit of a struggle, but I'm slowly getting into the habit of it. I'm hoping that by taking better care of myself, I'll be able to stay focused and productive in school.

entries.title: Memory lane
entries.entry: I was looking through some old photos today and it brought back a lot of memories. It was nice to reminisce about the good times and it made me appreciate the present even more. It's important to take a step back and appreciate the moments we have now, because they won't last forever.

entries.title: Freewriting
entries.entry: Today was a pretty chill day. I didn't have too much school work and I was able to relax a bit. I'm feeling a bit overwhelmed with all the assignments I have to do, but I'm trying to stay positive and take it one step at a time. I'm also trying to make time for myself and do things that make me happy.

entries.title: Mindful moments
entries.entry: I've been trying to be more mindful lately. I've been taking a few moments each day to just be present and appreciate the little things. It's been really helpful in reducing my stress levels and helping me stay focused. I'm also trying to be more mindful of my thoughts and be kinder to myself.

entries.title: Social connections
entries.entry: I've been trying to stay connected with my friends and family, even though we can't meet up in person. We've been having video calls and sending each other messages to stay in touch. It's been really nice to catch up and talk about our lives. It's also been a great way to stay connected and support each other during this difficult time.
